<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="191" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,753]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,150,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterolateral margin of pronotum with solid black stripe along all of its extension. Anterolateral margin punctured dorsally. Cicatrices of pronotum with black punctures delimiting anterior sulci (
<figureCitation box="[1235,1339,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[234,1349,198,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[218,1370,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Dorsal and ventral view. H. angulatus sp. n. A–B; H. bitumidus sp. n. C–D; H. clavatum sp. n. E–F; H. crassimarginatum sp. n. G–H; H. cristatus sp. n. I–J; H. dorsocarinatus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777096/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 18A</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with anterior margin yellow (
<figureCitation box="[534,639,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[234,1349,198,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[218,1370,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Dorsal and ventral view. H. angulatus sp. n. A–B; H. bitumidus sp. n. C–D; H. clavatum sp. n. E–F; H. crassimarginatum sp. n. G–H; H. cristatus sp. n. I–J; H. dorsocarinatus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777096/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 18A</figureCitation>
). Body ventrally with dark lines faded (
<figureCitation box="[1089,1192,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[234,1349,198,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-20@29.[218,1370,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 18. Dorsal and ventral view. H. angulatus sp. n. A–B; H. bitumidus sp. n. C–D; H. clavatum sp. n. E–F; H. crassimarginatum sp. n. G–H; H. cristatus sp. n. I–J; H. dorsocarinatus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777096/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 18B</figureCitation>
). Male genitalia (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1849,1873]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,495,1809]" captionTargetId="figure-87@3.[151,1436,480,1823]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hypoxys angulatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. Abbteviations: dr—dorsal rim; gp—superior process of the genital cup; pa—parameres; proc—proctiger; vr—ventral rim (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777060/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 1A–D</figureCitation>
). Dorsal rim of the pygophore with two slightly rounded expansions (
<figureCitation box="[1019,1109,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1849,1873]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,495,1809]" captionTargetId="figure-87@3.[151,1436,480,1823]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hypoxys angulatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. Abbteviations: dr—dorsal rim; gp—superior process of the genital cup; pa—parameres; proc—proctiger; vr—ventral rim (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777060/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup elongated, curved ventrally; ventral margin with a medial small rounded process; adjacent to dorsal rim; visible in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[323,446,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1849,1873]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,495,1809]" captionTargetId="figure-87@3.[151,1436,480,1823]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hypoxys angulatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. Abbteviations: dr—dorsal rim; gp—superior process of the genital cup; pa—parameres; proc—proctiger; vr—ventral rim (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777060/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 1A–C</figureCitation>
). Paramere triangular; anterior lobe short and truncated, posterior lobe developed and triangular; stalk with a medial inner carina reaching apex of anterior lobe; posterior lobe carinated (
<figureCitation box="[1200,1318,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1849,1873]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,495,1809]" captionTargetId="figure-87@3.[151,1436,480,1823]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hypoxys angulatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. Abbteviations: dr—dorsal rim; gp—superior process of the genital cup; pa—parameres; proc—proctiger; vr—ventral rim (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777060/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 1B–C</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with dorsolateral dense tufts of long setae separated by median flat slightly rugose area with sparse setae; posterior face barrel-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[314,435,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1849,1873]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,495,1809]" captionTargetId="figure-87@3.[151,1436,480,1823]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hypoxys angulatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. Abbteviations: dr—dorsal rim; gp—superior process of the genital cup; pa—parameres; proc—proctiger; vr—ventral rim (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777060/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 1A–D</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim median excavation deep and emarginated; expansions arched, large, with inner right angles, and surpassing level of posterolateral angles in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[961,1047,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1849,1873]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,495,1809]" captionTargetId="figure-87@3.[151,1436,480,1823]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hypoxys angulatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. Abbteviations: dr—dorsal rim; gp—superior process of the genital cup; pa—parameres; proc—proctiger; vr—ventral rim (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777060/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Female unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="191" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,753]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,510,536]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Comments.</emphasis>
This species belongs to the group with triangular paramere, together with 
<taxonomicName authority="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1191,1436,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ventrotuberculatus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1191,1436,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">H. ventrotuberculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,214,547,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,214,547,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[229,342,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[240,1340,194,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-23@28.[232,1355,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 17. Hypoxys ventrotuberculatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore;A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777094/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Figs. 17B</figureCitation>
). The 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[412,556,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angulatus">
<emphasis box="[412,556,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">H. angulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the anterior lobe of the paramere short (long in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1136,1379,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ventrotuberculatus">
<emphasis box="[1136,1379,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">H. ventrotuberculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and posterior lobe long (short in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[471,715,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ventrotuberculatus">
<emphasis box="[471,715,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">H. ventrotuberculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); also superior process of the genital cup with a short process in ventral margin (two processes in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[523,766,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ventrotuberculatus">
<emphasis box="[523,766,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">H. ventrotuberculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<figureCitation box="[781,882,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[240,1340,194,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-23@28.[232,1355,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 17. Hypoxys ventrotuberculatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore;A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777094/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 17B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="191" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,753]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,655,681]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Etymology.</emphasis>
A reference to the angular shape of the dorsal margin of the superior process of genital cup and inner angles of the expansions of the ventral rim of the pygophore.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
